(110, 2, '2015-12-01', '12:56:09', '<p><strong>SHIMLA:&nbsp;</strong>&nbsp;Himachal Pradesh&#39;s popular tourist destinations Shimla and Manali received rainfall today, pushing down the temperatures by several notches.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nShimla and its nearby places like Kufri and Narkanda have been experiencing rainfall since morning, according to a Met official.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nManali too received rain today, the official added.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&quot;High-altitude areas of Lahaul and Spiti, Chamba, Kullu, Kinnaur and Shimla districts were having snowfall since Thursday evening,&quot; the official said.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nKeylong, the headquarters of Lahaul and Spiti, recorded about one cm of snow, while it was two cm in Kalpa in Kinnaur district.<br />\r\n<br />\r\nShimla recorded a low of 4.3 degrees Celsius, while it was minus 0.7 degree in Keylong, 0.0 degree in Kalpa and 0.2 degrees Celsius in Manali, which saw 16 mm of rain.</p>\r\n', 'Rains in Shimla Manali  Mercury Dips', 0, 0, NULL, 0, 1, 0),
